									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ericolson/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/EO-LitHub-Photo-e1730406566962-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/EO-LitHub-Photo-e1730406566962-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Eric Olson" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ericolson/">Eric Olson</a></h6>
										Eric Olson is a novelist and journalist based in Seattle. You can find his writing in <em>The New York Times</em>, <em>The Washington Post</em>, <em>The Millions</em>, <em>The Daily Beast</em>, <em>The Seattle Times</em> and elsewhere. Learn more about him at ericolsonwriting.com.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="http://www.ericolsonwriting.com" target="_blank" class="external">http://www.ericolsonwriting.com</a>
				    					</div>
				    														</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
